The paper discusses fundamental limits and coding methods for wire tap channels, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) communities. The paper specifically focuses on the use of LDPC codes, which are a type of error-correcting code commonly used in communication systems (cs.CC). The paper also discusses practical applications of the proposed codes, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and multimedia (cs.MM), as secure communication is important in both fields.
